The AVPN market associate will focus on supporting the penetration and expansion of AVPN outreach and engagement in Southeast Asia, as well as maximizing the potential benefits for new and existing members of AVPN through active programme and product design and implementation. The role requires an effective communicator with an adaptable growth mindset, initiative and commitment to growing the AVPN footprint in Southeast Asia. This position reports to the Southeast Asia Director and/or the Chief Operating Officer in lieu.

Approximately 50% of the Associate뭩 time will be directed to support the development of Southeast Asia markets:
 Support market representatives in Southeast Asian markets in their engagement of prospect and current members and partners
 Conduct team communications with members/prospects/partners to answer their inquiries with the guidance of market representatives, including email replies, relevant eDMs and other mass emails as needed
 Work with market and product teams to design and implement new engagement opportunities including roundtable discussions, workshops, webinars and seminars, to meet grant deliverables and/or quality and outreach objectives
 Maintain and manage CRM data with Digital Transformation team support for effective use by market representatives and senior management.
 Actively monitoring and documenting the engagement by members through data-oriented methods, e.g. designing profiles of members, collection of feedback and engagement data, etc.
 Preparing internal reports and presentations to support the Chief Operating Officer and/or specific market representatives on an as-needed basis.
 Attend and represent AVPN at external sector events to achieve objectives of this role
Related to Southeast Asia, approximately 50% of the Associate뭩 time will be directed to develop the outreach/penetration of key thematic platforms in the subregion:
 Desk-based research and identifying outreach approach for prospective new members or partners for Southeast Asia markets and key thematic platforms
 Support the Platform heads and market representatives to engage and mobilise members through identifying opportunities for connections, collaboration and visibility for member activities, particularly in Gender Platform, CV19 Platform and Climate Action Platform.